name: Massachusetts

processing_metadata.description: Official Massachusetts DMV processing rules and validation requirements

global_rules.code_system: Massachusetts uses code numbers to identify plate types
global_rules.character_restrictions: Uses both O and 0 - O with letters, 0 with numbers
global_rules.processing_note: Processing rules vary by plate type and are defined in the CSV matrix. Custom processing types will be provided separately.
global_rules.emergency_vehicle_rule: Reject images of Marked Emergency Vehicles for codes 61, 62, 63, 72
global_rules.stacked_characters_rule: Code 32 (Commercial): KEY all stacked. Code 66 (Livery): KEY stacked LV. Codes 72, 73: OMIT stacked STATE
global_rules.slanted_characters_rule: Code 63 (Authority): If 4+ slanted characters, KEY ONLY FIRST 3
global_rules.omit_letter_t_rule: Code 63 (Authority): DO NOT KEY letter "T" on left side
global_rules.omit_stickers_rule: Code 82 (Dealer): OMIT "D" sticker. Code 84 (Repair): OMIT "R" sticker
global_rules.special_text_omission: Code 46 (Passenger): DO NOT INCLUDE "EX POW" or "US CONGRESS"
global_rules.lightning_bolt_rule: Code 46 (Passenger): Replace Lightning Bolt with FORWARD SLASH "/"
global_rules.key_all_characters_rule: Most plate types: All characters must be keyed unless specific omit rule applies

processing_metadata.character_modifications: Allows letter O on personalized plates
